Feb 8 2009 	A unique alternative	We stayed 2 nights in the Library Suite to celebrate a special birthday. I agree with the other reviewers concerning the uniqueness of such a place, the consideration shown by the owners, the attempts to think of everything one might need etc. We never saw or heard another guest, despite it being a full house. The location near LIncoln Center is superb. The only drawback is the lack of ability by the guest to control the use of the fireplace. The reason we chose this inn rather than a standard hotel was because of the fireplace. We were so looking forward to using it but discovered that use was limited to 11 AM to 5 PM and that the fire had to be set by the owners (due to insurance regulations). I can understand if they need to maintain this policy but I feel it should be noted on their website when they offer suites with working fireplaces. It was a major disappointment for us.	
