Jan 11 2008 	Wonderful home away from home	My family spent the Christmas holiday week in the Vermont Suite. The reviews were all on target. The accomodations worked well for our family with the separate living room and downstairs bedroom. The bedroom was so quiet...the walls must be so thick because we heard none of the neighbors or street traffic. It was very nice to have the small, but well stocked kitchen available. We ended up eating breakfast at &quot;home&quot; everyday. My sons and I loved the quiche and pastries provided, which along with orange juice and milk, started our day off well. There were lots of goodies provided...we especially enjoyed the chocolate cake and apple pie that were waiting when we returned after a long day of sightseeing. The location of the Inn is perfect. We bought 7 day passes for the subway/buses. The subway stop is closeby on 72nd, but we opted to take buses in order to see the city (which is very convenient to the Inn as well). There are loads of wonderful places to eat nearby. We enjoyed Citrus (Cuban with an Asian twist)---they had a tasty brunch on Sunday. Also, stop by Buttercup Bake Shop (on 72nd between Broadway and Columbus) if you haven't had enough sweets at the Inn. The cupcakes were delicious and the peanut butter cookies were so good! Within a short walk are shopping, an AMC theatre, Barnes &amp; Noble, Lincoln Center...I could go on. We walked to The Metropolitan Museum of Art (through Central Park) and the Museum of Natural History. The best part about the location is the quiet. Just spend some time in Times Square or walking in crowds on Fifth Avenue and you'll appreciate the fact that you are staying at the Inn. My only suggestion...and only negative comment...was mentioned by another reviewer about the bed in the Vermont Suite. I found it a little too stiff and sometimes awoke with aches if I slept on my side. Perhaps switching to a Select Comfort AIr Mattress or similar type of mattress might be an option considering logistics of moving a mattress up/down the steep spiral staircase. Other than this one negative, the stay was just perfect. I would recommend Inn New York City to anyone who wants to experience living in New York rather than staying in a hotel room.	
