Oct 13 2007	Absolute perfection!	This is simply the most amazing place to stay. The hotel has no sign outside, so it is incredibly discreet, and a little like walking into your own house in NY. As you step into the house it gives you a good impression of what to expect during your stay - classical music, antiques and sweets for you to help yourself to when arriving or leaving (which became a tradition!). Ruth was a fantastic host - there just when you wanted her but gave the right amount of privacy. We stayed in the Opera suite which was on the ground floor. It is around 30 metres long, with a grand piano complete with music books and scores, a living area, a kitchen, bathroom with jacuzzi bath, bedroom and private terrace at the back. Absolute luxury!! Every need was catered for and we did not have to ask for anything additional during our stay.The kitchen was fully stocked with breakfast items, including bagels, jams, croissants, fresh fruit and orange juice, but there was also a whole host of other items including freshly baked cake (a new one every day!), wine, bottled water, sweets... I could go on and on! The hotel itself is situated on a quiet street on the Upper West Side, with the subway situated one block away about a 3 minute walk. The subway is four stops away from Times Square on the local line, or one on the express line, and from Times Square you can get a connection to pretty much any line to take you anywhere you want to go. The hotel itself is also only about a 15 minute walk from Central Park - the walk is really pretty and takes you past all of the brownstone buildings in the area.I could go on and on about how wonderful this place is for hours but needless to say it is absolutely highly recommended. We would go back in an instant.	
